Description . Measurements. Males: 3.6–4.1 mm ( holotype 3.9 mm ), females: 3.7–4.5 mm . Body (
Fig. 87
) elongate, parallel, dorsal side glabrous, elytra with sparse short setae on apical and lateral slopes. Body, antennae and legs metallic bluish-black, extreme apical margin of femora brownish, male abdomen yellow with ventrite I black (rarely only anterior margin of ventrite I darkened), female abdomen completely yellow.

Prosternal process not visible between procoxae. Posterior margin of last ventrite with two deep incisions (
Fig. 122
).

Aedeagus symmetrical, middle part slightly divergent apically, apex triangular strongly bent down, with the tip rounded (
Fig. 119
). Internal sac relatively simple, with only one long thin sclerite (
Fig. 128
).

Female. Interocular space wider, 2.85 times as wide as transverse diameter of eye. Last ventrite widely rounded with shallow anteroapical emarginations (
Fig. 124
). Pygidium subtriangular with widely rounded lateral margins and apex (
Fig. 123
). Sternite VIII transversely oval with setae along anterior margin, tignum slender 2.1 as long as sternite VIII (
Fig. 121
). Spermatheca: nodulus gradually convergent to to C-shaped cornu, proximal spermathecal duct straight, slightly wider basally (
Fig. 120
).
